<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>PayPal Set-Up</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
    <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
            <xar:if condition="file_exists('modules/mail/xarimages/admin.gif')" >
                <img src="modules/mail/xarimages/admin.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
            <xar:else />
                <img src="modules/mail/xarimages/admin_generic.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
            </xar:if>
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>The Paypal IPN module will provide an instant payment notification for Xaraya in the event that someone has purchased something and paid through Paypal.  The module itself only notifies any other module that are hooked to it based on a create hook that an event has happened.  It is up to the individual modules themselves to track whether the event was correct as in payment price, etc.  This is a utility module to be used with multiple modules as a pass through for collecting payment information.</xar:mlstring>
		</div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>From the menu, you have one choice. </xar:mlstring>
            <p><xar:mlstring>"Modify Configuration".  From this menu option, you can update the necessary configuration options, such as your whether to send you an email on receipt or to test the module before going live on a production basis.</xar:mlstring></p>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
			<xar:mlstring>There are no blocks included at this time.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>The Paypal IPN module will send a create hook throughout the system to notify other modules that an event has happened.  Check your hook configuration if problems exists on notification.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-norm-outline xar-accent" style="text-align: center; padding: 0.5em 1em 0.5em 1em; margin-top: 5px;">
            <xar:mlstring>Extended information about this module can be found here. [modules module]</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>